# Rust Testing

- Add or update tests for every business logic change and bug fix.
- For critical flows, cover at least one success case and one failure case.
- Prefer deterministic tests: explicit fixtures, no hidden global state, stable timing.
- Keep integration tests behavior-focused; avoid asserting internal implementation details.
- Add regression tests for previously reported bugs when reproducible.
- If tests are infeasible, document why and provide concise manual verification steps.
